Documentation: Enables scanning of pasted images for DLP.

Name: kSCTAuditing
Documentation:
This requires backend infrastructure and a data collection policy.
Non-Chrome builds should not use Chrome's infrastructure.

Name: kEnterpriseIframeDlpRulesSupport
Documentation:
Controls whether the iFrame parent url chain initiated from the active frame
will be attached to DLP scan requests.

Name: kSafetyHubLocalPasswordsModule
Documentation: Enables the local passwords module in Safety Hub.

Name: kAutofillAiIgnoreGeoIp
Documentation:
If enabled, no GeoIp requirements are imposed for AutofillAi.
Note that this feature can be modified as follows (all assuming that
`kAutofillAiIgnoreGeoIp` is enabled):
- If both `kAutofillAiIgnoreGeoIpAllowlist` and
  `kAutofillAiIgnoreGeoIpBlocklist` are empty, then all geo IPs are
  permitted.
- If only `kAutofillAiIgnoreGeoIpBlocklist` is non-empty, then all geo ips
  but those in `kAutofillAiIgnoreGeoIpBlocklist` are permitted.
- If `kAutofillAiIgnoreGeoIpAllowlist` is non-empty, then only geo ips in
  `kAutofillAiIgnoreGeoIpAllowlist` are permitted.

Both the allowlist and the blocklist are expected to consist of
comma-separated uppercase two-digit country codes (see documentation of
`GeoIpCountryCode`.)

Name: kClientSideDetectionKillswitch
Documentation:
Killswitch for client side phishing detection. Since client side models are
run on a large fraction of navigations, crashes due to the model are very
impactful, even if only a small fraction of users have a bad version of the
model. This Finch flag allows us to remediate long-tail component versions
while we fix the root cause. This will also halt the model distribution from
OptimizationGuide.

Name: kDocumentIsolationPolicy
Documentation:
Enables Document-Isolation-Policy (DIP).
https://github.com/WICG/document-isolation-policy

Name: kFreezingFollowsDiscardOptOut
Documentation:
When enabled, the freezing policy won't freeze pages that are opted out of
tab discarding.

Name: kInternalMediaSession
Documentation:
Enables the internal Media Session logic without enabling the Media Session
service.

Name: kAutofillSupportLastNamePrefix
Documentation: Enables using custom name model with last name prefixes support.

Name: kPostMessageFirstPartyToThirdPartyDifferentBucketSameOriginBlocked
Documentation:
Whether first-party to third-party different-bucket same-origin post messages
are blocked.

Name: kCustomizeTabGroupColorPalette
Documentation:
When enabled, allows parsing of `tab_group_color_palette` theme key, else
ignores it.

Name: kEnableRtcpReporting
Documentation:
Controls whether the Mirroring Service will fetch, analyze, and store
information on the quality of the session using RTCP logs.

Name: kPasswordFormGroupedAffiliations
Documentation: Enables offering credentials for filling across grouped domains.

Name: kCCSlimming
Documentation:
Kill switch for a bunch of optimizations for cc-slimming project.
Please see crbug.com/335450599 for more details.

Name: kPrivacySandboxSettings4
Documentation: Enables the fourth release of the Privacy Sandbox settings.

Name: kAndroidAppIntegrationModule
Documentation:
The maximum number of times the auxiliary search promo card can be visible to
the user.

Name: kAlwaysUseAudioManagerOutputFramesPerBuffer
Documentation:
Use buffer size from AudioManager.PROPERTY_OUTPUT_FRAMES_PER_BUFFER for
optimal output frame size.

Name: kJumpStartOmnibox
Documentation:
Accelerates time from cold start to focused Omnibox on low-end devices,
prioritizing Omnibox focus and background initialization.

Name: kTabstripComboButton
Documentation:
Controls where tab search lives in the browser. By default, the tab search
feature lives in the tab strip. The feature moves to the toolbar button if
the user is in the US and `kLaunchedTabSearchToolbarButton` is enabled or if
`kTabstripComboButton` is enabled and `kTabSearchToolbarButton` is true.

Name: kAllowContentInitiatedDataUrlNavigations
Documentation: Please keep features in alphabetical order.

Name: kHistoryClustersInternalsPage
Documentation: Enables the history clusters internals page.

Name: kTransparentIconWorkaround
Documentation:
Workaround for an issue in Windows where icons with fully transparent
pixels are rendered as black squares. See https://crbug.com/441293180
Used as a killswitch in case an issue is discovered with the implementation.

Name: kPreloadServingMetrics
Documentation:
Kill switch, which enables reporting serving metrics of preloads.
(crbug.com/360094997)

TODO(crbug.com/360094997): Remove it after confirming stability.

Name: kAutofillAndPasswordsInSameSurface
Documentation:
Guards the refactoring to allow showing Autofill and Password suggestions in
the same surface instead of being mutually exclusive.

Name: kAndroidOpenIncognitoAsWindow
Documentation: Feature that enables opening Incognito windows.

Name: kNtpComposebox
Documentation:
If overridden to false, disables the feature (kill switch). If true, enables
the feature.

Name: kEarlyFullScreenVideoOptimization
Documentation: Detect and mark a single full screen video during overlay processing.

Name: kResumeBackgroundVideo
Documentation:
Let videos be resumed via remote controls (for example, the notification)
when in background.

Name: kMemoryMeasurementInFreezingPolicy
Documentation:
When enabled, the freezing policy measures memory usage. This exists to
quantify the overhead of memory measurement in a holdback study.

Name: kExtensionsToolbarZeroState
Documentation:
If enabled, guide users with zero extensions installed to explore the
benefits of extensions.
Displays an IPH anchored to the Extensions Toolbar Button, and replaces the
extensions submenu with an alternative submenu to recommend extensions.

Name: kAutofillRetryImageFetchOnFailure
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome will try to fetch payment account image resources again
upon failure. The number of attempts is a controllable parameter. This is a
kill-switch.
TODO(crbug.com/40276036): Clean up after M139 branch (June 23, 2025).

Name: kEnableBandAClickiness
Documentation: Enable sending clickiness data in B&A requests.

Name: kSkiaGraphite
Documentation:
Enable Skia Graphite. This will use the Dawn backend by default, but can be
overridden with command line flags for testing on non-official developer
builds. See --skia-graphite-backend flag in gpu_switches.h.
Note: This can also be overridden by
--enable-skia-graphite & --disable-skia-graphite.

Name: kAutofillAiIgnoreLocale
Documentation: If enabled, no locale requirements are imposed for AutofillAi.

Name: kWebRtcUnmuteTracksWhenPacketArrives
Documentation:
This feature unumutes a track when a packet arrives instead of after
setRemoteDescription.

Name: kSharedHighlightingManager
Documentation: Enables the new SharedHighlightingManager refactoring.

Name: kAimServerRequestOnIdentityChangeEnabled
Documentation: If enabled, makes a server request on identity changes.

Name: kTpcdMetadataGrants
Documentation:
Whether to enable the use of 3PC based on 3PCD metadata grants delivered via
component updater.

Name: kFedCmIframeOrigin
Documentation:
For cross-site iframes, sends the top-level origin to the IDP and parses
an optional returned boolean indicating whether it is part of the same
client to allow for UI decisions based on the boolean.

Name: kUpdateIsMainFrameOriginRecentlyAccessed
Documentation:
When enabled, the browser checks if a navigation URL is in any navigation
entry. If so, it sets the
`IS_MAIN_FRAME_ORIGIN_RECENTLY_ACCESSED` load flag.
Note that this flag is only set for metric collection.

Name: kDelayOnProfileCreatedForFullBrowserTransition
Documentation:
Enables delaying the call to FullBrowserTransitionManager::OnProfileCreated()
until after BrowserContextDependencyManager::CreateBrowserContextServices()
in ProfileImpl::OnLocaleReady(). This change is thought to avoid creating
certain KeyedServices before they are properly initialized, but is flagged
guarded in case it causes unexpected issues.

Name: kAutofillPrioritizeSaveCardOverMandatoryReauth
Documentation:
When enabled, this feature prioritizes showing the save card bubble over the
mandatory re-auth bubble when both are applicable.

Name: kEsbAsASyncedSetting
Documentation:
Makes the Enhanced Protection a syncable setting.
Check the design doc (go/esb-as-a-synced-setting-dd) for further details.

Name: kFilterInstalledAppsWebAppMatching
Documentation: Enables installed web app matching for getInstalledRelatedApps API.

Name: kImageSearchSuggestionThumbnail
Documentation:
Please do not add more features to this "big blob" list.
Instead, use the categorized and alphabetized lists below this "big blob".
You can create a new category if none of the existing ones fit.

Name: kMbiOverrideTaskRunnerHandle
Documentation:
If enabled, base::SingleThreadTaskRunner::GetCurrentDefault() and
base::SequencedTaskRunner::GetCurrentDefault() returns the current active
per-ASG task runner instead of the per-thread task runner.

Name: kStreamlineRendererInit
Documentation: Reduces the work done during renderer initialization.

Name: kEnableEdidBasedDisplayIds
Documentation:
TODO(gildekel): A temporary flag to control whether EDID-based (vs.
port-based) display IDs are generated per display. Remove once the migration
process it complete (b/193019614).

Name: kLocalNetworkAccessChecksWebSockets
Documentation:
Enables Local Network Access checks for WebSockets.
Blocks local network requests without user permission to prevent exploitation
of vulnerable local devices.

Spec: https://wicg.github.io/local-network-access/

Name: kMeasurementNoticeModalFeature
Documentation: Restricted Notice Features

Name: kEmulateLoadStartedForInspectorOncePerResource
Documentation:
If enabled, the body of `EmulateLoadStartedForInspector` is executed only
once per Resource per ResourceFetcher, and thus duplicated network load
entries in DevTools caused by `EmulateLoadStartedForInspector` are removed.
https://crbug.com/1502591

Name: kAutofillAiSavePromptSurvey
Documentation:
When enabled, a HaTS survey is shown after the save prompt for a walletable
entity was interacted with.

Name: kOriginMatcherNewCopyAssignment
Documentation:
When enabled, OriginMatcher::operator= will use the new, hopefully faster
implementation that does not serialize and deserialize all the rules.

Name: kNtpMiddleSlotPromoDismissal
Documentation:
If enabled, middle slot promo will be dismissed from New Tab Page until new
promo message is populated

Name: kAndroidSurfaceControl
Documentation:
Use android SurfaceControl API for managing display compositor's buffer queue
and using overlays on Android. Also used by webview to disable surface
SurfaceControl.

Name: kLastVSyncArgsKillswitch
Documentation:
Stops BeginFrame issue to use |last_vsync_interval_| instead of the current
set of BeginFrameArgs.
TODO(b/333940735): Should be removed if the issue isn't fixed.

Name: kReloadSelectionModel
Documentation:
When enabled, reloading using the toolbar button, hotkey, and web contents
context menu will only reload the active tab. The tab context menu will still
use the selection model to reload.

Name: kPwaNavigationCapturing
Documentation: Enables user link capturing on all desktop platforms.

Name: kVisitedURLRankingService
Documentation: Core feature flag for Visited URL Ranking service.

Name: kMatchSourceAudioChannelLayout
Documentation:
Allows Chrome to reconfigure the sink to match the channel count of the
source audio data. This ensures opening of an audio output stream to match
the source audio data channels, to signal to the downstream audio
subsystem that the audio must be processed according to the source audio
channel count.
TODO(crbug.com/445215599): This should be replaced with a MediaClient
mechanism if it works as intended.

Name: kPrerenderMoreCorrectSpeculativeRFHCreation
Documentation:
A misunderstanding when fixing crbug.com/40076091 meant that non-speculative
RFHs were being created with a provisional RenderFrame in the renderer. This
is nominally harmless, but can crash prerenders if devtool's network
overrides feature is enabled. Guarded by a feature since fixing this new bug
might reintroduce the previous crashes.

Name: kDeprecatedExternalPickerFunction
Documentation: Use the old-style opening of an External Picker when uploading files.

Name: kRenderSizeInScoreAdBrowserSignals
Documentation:
Enable the optional renderSize field in the browserSignals parameter of
scoreAd function of Protected Audience API.
See explainer:
https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/blob/main/FLEDGE.md#23-scoring-bids

Name: kContextualTasks
Documentation: Enables the contextual tasks side panel while browsing.

Name: kNtpNextFeatures
Documentation: If enabled, the features of NTP Next (AI action chips etc.) will be shown.

Name: kAutofillAcrossIframesIosThrottling
Documentation:
Throttles child frame extraction to a maximum number of child frames that
can be extracted by applying the following rules: (1) remove the child frames
from an individual form that busts the limit and (2) stop extracting child
frames on other forms once the limit is reached across forms.

Name: kSideBySideDropTargetNudge
Documentation: Feature and params to control the "nudge" behavior of drop targets.

Name: kProcessSelectionDeferringConditions
Documentation:
When enabled, ProcessSelectionDeferringConditions will be run. This allows
the embedder to provide conditions that may delay the final process selection
until the conditions have their results.

Name: kDataSharingEnableUpdateChromeUI
Documentation:
Feature flag to show UI that prompts the user to update Chrome when the
version is out of date.
Note: Do not clean up this feature as it is meant to be used in unforeseen
situations as a kill switch in future from finch when the shared tab groups
feature becomes incompatible for the current chrome client.

Name: kNtpDriveModuleHistorySyncRequirement
Documentation: If enabled, the NTP Drive module does not require sync.

Name: kEnableWebTransportDraft07
Documentation: Enables draft-07 version of WebTransport over HTTP/3.

Name: kDisableTLSResumption
Documentation: Disables TLS resumption.

Name: kGCMAvoidConnectionWhenNetworkUnavailable
Documentation: When enabled, the connection to the server won't be initiated when offline.

Name: kCacheStorageParallelOps
Documentation:
Enables support for parallel cache_storage operations via the
"max_shared_ops" fieldtrial parameter.

Name: kComposeTextOutputAnimation
Documentation: Enables animation of text output. Applies only to on-device evaluation.

Name: kOnDeviceModelValidation
Documentation: TODO: crbug.com/428242339 - Clean this up once this is stabilized.

Name: kSeparateLocalAndAccountThemes
Documentation: If enabled, distinguishes between local and account themes.

Name: kDataSharingAccountDataMigration
Documentation:
Migration flag of the SharedTabGroupAccountDataSpecifics into
//components/data_sharing.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformIosModuleRankerSplitBySurface
Documentation: Feature flag for having separate models for the Start and NTP surface.

Name: kDevToolsAiAssistancePerformanceAgent
Documentation: Whether the DevTools AI Assistance Performance Agent is enabled.

Name: kAutofillSyncEwalletAccounts
Documentation:
When enabled, eWallet accounts are synced from the Google Payments servers
and displayed on the payment methods settings page.

Name: kAutofillBetterLocalHeuristicPlaceholderSupport
Documentation:
When enabled, the placeholder is not considered a label fallback on the
renderer side anymore. Instead, local heuristic will match regexes against
either the label or the placeholder, depending on how high quality the label
is. If no matche is found, local heuristics fall back to the other value.
This feature can be thought of as "lightweight" multi-label support.
TODO(crbug.com/320965828): Remove when launched.

Name: kServiceWorkerClientUrlIsCreationUrl
Documentation:
(crbug.com/41337436): Enabled feature will have the ServiceWorker Client.url
property be the creation URL. This means it does not reflect changes to the
URL made by history.pushState() or similar history APIs.
When disabled the ServiceWorker Client.url property will be the document URL
including changes to history.pushState().

Name: kHttpsFirstModeV2ForEngagedSites
Documentation:
Enables HTTPS-First Mode for engaged sites. No-op if HttpsFirstModeV2 or
HTTPS-Upgrades is disabled.

Name: kImageAnnotationServiceExperimental
Documentation: Whether or not to override service parameters for experimentation.

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessForNavigationsWarningOnly
Documentation:
Enables Private Network Access checks in warning mode for navigations.

Does nothing if `kPrivateNetworkAccessForNavigations` is disabled.

If both this and `kPrivateNetworkAccessForNavigations` are enabled, then PNA
preflight requests for navigations are not required to succeed. If
one fails, a warning is simply displayed in DevTools.

Name: kWebRtcAV1HWEncode
Documentation:
When enabled, allows AV1 HW encoding to be used for WebRTC streams, if the
platform accelerator supports encoding of AV1.

Name: kThemesBatchUpload
Documentation: If enabled, offers batch upload of local themes upon sign in.

Name: kInvalidateSearchEngineChoiceOnDeviceRestoreDetection
Documentation:
Invalidates old search engine choices when Chrome detects that it has been
transferred to a new device.

Name: kLowerQuicMaxPacketSize
Documentation: If enabled, we will use QUIC with a smaller MTU.

Name: kPrerender2WarmUpCompositorForBookmarkBar
Documentation:
If enabled, requests the compositor warm-up (crbug.com/41496019) for
each prerender trigger.

Name: kUseLibunwindstackNativeUnwinderAndroid
Documentation:
Use the LibunwindstackNativeUnwinderAndroid for only browser main thread, and
only on Android.

Name: kEnableExtensionInstallPolicyFetching
Documentation: Used to enable extension install policy support.

Name: kShopCardImpressionLimits
Documentation: Impression limits on ShopCards

Name: kUseAndroidOverlayForSecureOnly
Documentation:
Use AndroidOverlay only if required for secure video playback. This requires
that |kOverlayFullscreenVideo| is true, else it is ignored.

Name: kHttpsFirstModeIncognito
Documentation:
Enables HTTPS-First Mode by default in Incognito Mode. (The related feature
kHttpsFirstModeIncognitoNewSettings controls whether new settings controls
are available for opting out of this default behavior.)

Name: kAccessibilityInlineLineSeparators
Documentation:
When populating the AccessibilityNodeInfo on Android, Clank will insert Line
Separator U+2028 characters in the text to denote soft line breaks.

Name: kOpenAllUrlsOrFilesOnDrop
Documentation: Fix for https://crbug.com/40927333.

Name: kSendCnameAliasesToSubresourceFilterFromRenderer
Documentation:
Performs additional SubresourceFilter checks when CNAME aliases are found
for the host of a requested URL.

Name: kCreateWarningShownClientSafeBrowsingReports
Documentation: Creates and sends CSBRRs when warnings are first shown to users.

Name: kMediaDrmPersistentLicense
Documentation:
An experimental feature to enable persistent-license type support in MediaDrm
when using Encrypted Media Extensions (EME) API.
TODO(xhwang): Remove this after feature launch. See http://crbug.com/493521

Name: kBluetoothBtsnoopInternals
Documentation:
Enables/disables the option to collect btsnoop log from
chrome://bluetooth-internals

Name: kEnterprisePasswordReuseUiRefresh
Documentation: Enables showing an updated Password Reuse UI for enterprise users.

Name: kUseNewServiceWorkerTaskQueue
Documentation: If enabled, use the new simpler, more efficient service worker task queue.

Name: kCommittedOriginEnforcements
Documentation:
Turn on enforcements based on tracking the list of committed origins in
ChildProcessSecurityPolicy::CanAccessMaybeOpaqueOrigin(). Note that this only
controls whether or not the new security checks take effect; when this is
off, the security check is still performed and compared to the legacy jail
and citadel check to collect data about possible mismatches. Requires
CommittedOriginTracking to also be turned on to take effect. See
https://crbug.com/40148776.

TODO(alexmos): Remove this feature flag once committed origin enforcements
are fully launched. For now, the feature is kept as a kill switch.

Name: kLaunchedHistoryEmbeddings
Documentation: Do not use. For test only.

Name: kFledgeEnableUnNoisedRealTimeReport
Documentation: Enable un-noised real time reporting for certain user settings.

Name: kWebPaymentsJustInTimePaymentApp
Documentation: Used to control whether allow crawling just-in-time installable payment app.

Name: kPrivacySandboxAdsAPIsM1Override
Documentation:
Enables exposure of the core milestone 1 (M1) APIs in the renderer without an
origin trial token: Attribution Reporting, FLEDGE, Topics.

Name: kToolbarHeightSidePanel
Documentation:
Enables a side panel that occupies the vertical space from the top of the
toolbar to the bottom of the browser. This is taller than the default side
panel, which occupies the space from the top of the WebContents to the bottom
of the browser.

Name: kIndexedDBCompressValuesWithSnappy
Documentation:
Use Snappy to compress values for IndexedDB before wiring them to the
browser.

Name: kRemoveSearchboxStatsParamFromPrefetchRequests
Documentation:
Kill switch to revert the fix of dropping searchbox stats (gs_lcrp) from
prefetch requests. See crbug.com/350939001.

Name: kNtpPhotosModuleCustomizedOptInTitle
Documentation: If enabled, a customized title will be shown on the opt-in card.

Name: kHandleMdmErrorsForDasherAccounts
Documentation: Feature to handle mdm errors on Enterprise and EDU accounts

Name: kFledgeOriginScopedKeys
Documentation: See https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/issues/1334

Name: kEnableStaticCTAPIEnforcement
Documentation:
Kill switch for Static CT Log (aka Tiled Log aka Sunlight)
enforcements in Certificate Transparency policy checks. If disabled, SCTs
from Static CT Logs will simply be ignored.

Name: kAutofillUseStructuralSignatureInsteadOfSecondary
Documentation:
Replaces the secondary signature with the structural signature for Uploads.
For Queries still only the secondary (alternative) signature is used.
TODO(crbug.com/431737839): Clean up when roll out finishes successfully.

Name: kWebAuthnActorCheck
Documentation:
This is used to enable an experiment to reject WebAuthn requests
when actor mode is on.

Name: kWalrusUseProdServer
Documentation: Enables Walrus Prod Server

Name: kUseSnappyForParkableStrings
Documentation:
Enabling this will cause parkable strings to use Snappy for compression iff
kCompressParkableStrings is enabled.

Name: kSendBeaconThrowForBlobWithNonSimpleType
Documentation: Make sendBeacon throw for a Blob with a non simple type.

Name: kCreateImageBitmapOrientationNone
Documentation:
When enabled, add a new option, {imageOrientation: 'none'}, to
createImageBitmap, which ignores the image orientation metadata of the source
and renders the image as encoded.

Name: kDesktopPWAsPreventClose
Documentation: If enabled, allow-listed PWAs cannot be closed manually by the user.

Name: kSynchronizedScrolling
Documentation:
Whether the compositor should attempt to sync with the scroll handlers before
submitting a frame.

Name: kDisableFacilitatedPaymentsMerchantAllowlist
Documentation:
When enabled, the check for matching the main frame domain with the
allowlisted domains will be disabled.

Name: kAsyncDns
Documentation: Enables the built-in DNS resolver.

Name: kYourSavedInfoBrandingInSettings
Documentation:
When enabled, updates the "Autofill and passwords" (or "Passwords and
autofill") labels and icons to "Your saved info".

Name: kWebUsbDeviceDetection
Documentation:
Enables runtime detection of USB devices which provide a WebUSB landing page
descriptor.

Name: kWebAuthnSignalApiHidePasskeys
Documentation:
Enables hiding passkeys instead of hard deleting them when reported as
obsolete by the signal API.

Name: kAutofillEnableNewCardBenefitsToggleText
Documentation: When enabled, the card benefits toggle in settings will show updated text.

Name: kPlusAddressParseExistingProfilesFromCreateResponse
Documentation:
When enabled, we check whether the server response to a Create call returned
information about existing profiles and return those as the parsing result.

Name: kAVDColorSpaceChanges
Documentation: Whether we should allow color space changes to flush AcceleratedVideoDecoder.

Name: kOptimizationGuideModelExecution
Documentation: Whether to enable model execution.

Name: kAblateSearchProviderWarmup
Documentation: Search and Suggest requests and params.

Name: kIPHDummyFeature
Documentation: A feature to ensure all arrays can contain at least one feature.

Name: kTranslateAutoSnackbars
Documentation:
Feature flag used to control the auto-always and auto-never snackbar
parameters (i.e. threshold and maximum-number-of).

Name: kWebViewEnableADPFRendererMain
Documentation:
If enabled, Renderer Main is included in the set of threads reported to the
HWUI. This feature works only when WebViewEnableADPF is enabled, otherwise
this is a no-op.

Name: kSerialSplitDtrAndRts
Documentation:
Splits DTR and RTS control signals. See crbug.com/420689824.
Can be disabled as a kill switch if needed.

Name: kQuickUnlockPinAutosubmitBackfill
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/1104164) - Remove this once most users have their preferences
backfilled.

Name: kUseAAudioInput
Documentation:
Enables loading and using AAudio instead of OpenSLES on compatible devices,
for audio input streams.

Name: kBrokerFileOperationsOnDiskCacheInNetworkService
Documentation:
Broker file operations on disk cache in the Network Service.
This is no-op if the network service is hosted in the browser process.

Name: kPauseBackgroundTimer
Documentation:
We plan to remove the background pause timer feature from WebMediaPlayerImpl.
We received reports that suggest that this feature's codepath hasn't been
exercised for a long time. This is a finch killswitch to rollback to the
previous behavior if we find any problems while disabling this feature.

Name: kMlUrlPiecewiseMappedSearchBlending
Documentation:
If enabled, (floating-point) ML model scores are mapped to (integral)
relevance scores by means of a piecewise function. This allows for the
integration of URL model scores with search traditional scores.

Name: kDocumentPictureInPictureAnimateResize
Documentation: Adds an animation to document picture-in-picture resizes.

Name: kLightweightNoStatePrefetch
Documentation: A feature to reduce the set of resources fetched by No-State Prefetch.

Name: kRestrictThreadPoolInBackground
Documentation:
Restrict the maximum number of concurrent ThreadPool tasks when a renderer is
low priority.

Name: kV8FlushBaselineCode
Documentation: Enables flushing of baseline code in V8.

Name: kOnDeviceModelCpuBackend
Documentation: Whether the CPU backend for the on-device model is enabled.

Name: kNtpAlphaBackgroundCollections
Documentation:
If enabled, alpha NTP backgrounds will show in Customize Chrome.
This is a development switch. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kPermissionHeuristicAutoGrant
Documentation: Enables heuristic auto-grant for permissions.

Name: kDarkenWebsitesCheckboxInThemesSetting
Documentation: Enables auto dark feature in theme settings.

Name: kAbusiveNotificationPermissionRevocation
Documentation: Enables notification permission revocation for abusive origins.

Name: kLiveCaptionUseGreedyTextStabilizer
Documentation:
Use a greedy text stabilizer to reduce flickering when translating partial
speech recognition results.

Name: kSigninWindows10DepreciationStateBypassForTesting
Documentation:
Set this flag to force the flow off on Windows 10 (a lot of bots run on
Windows 10) - to avoid having generic tests having a per platform
expectations.

Name: kRestrictIsReadyToPayQuery
Documentation:
Used to control whether the `kCanMakePaymentEnabled` pref being false will
stop the IsReadyToPay query from being sent to payment handlers.

Name: kURLPatternDummyURLCanonicalization
Documentation:
If enabled, URLPattern will use standard defined dummy URL canonicalization
to canonicalize URL properties. See https://crbug.com/409350827

Name: kAndroidHDR
Documentation:
Feature controlling whether or not HDR is enabled on Android.
TODO(crbug.com/40263227): Leave this as a kill switch until Android U
ships.

Name: kIsolatedWebApps
Documentation: LINT.IfChange

Name: kAndroidBcivBottomControls
Documentation:
If this flag is enabled, AndroidBrowserControlsInViz and
BottomControlsRefactor with the "Dispatch yOffset" variation must also be
enabled.

Name: kDevToolsAiCodeCompletion
Documentation: Whether the DevTools AI Code Completion is enabled.

Name: kReusePrerenderingProcessForMainFrames
Documentation:
When enabled, try to reuse any same-site process that is hosting
only prerendered frames for main-frame navigations.

Name: kWebViewAsyncDrawOnly
Documentation:
Trial to disable synchronous draw for synchronous compositor (ie Android
WebView).

Name: kAutofillPopupDontAcceptNonVisibleEnoughSuggestion
Documentation:
If the feature is enabled, before triggering suggestion acceptance, the row
view checks that a substantial portion of its content was visible for some
minimum required period.
TODO(crbug.com/337222641): During cleaning up, in the popup row view remove
emitting of "Autofill.AcceptedSuggestionDesktopRowViewVisibleEnough".

Name: kDiscoFeedEndpoint
Documentation: Use the new DiscoFeed endpoint.

Name: kSiteIsolationForCrossOriginOpenerPolicy
Documentation:
Controls whether to isolate sites of documents that specify an eligible
Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy header.  Note that this is only intended to be
used on Android, which does not use strict site isolation. See
https://crbug.com/1018656.

Name: kJavaScriptPromiseTry
Documentation: Enables the Promise.try proposal.

Name: kAutofillRelaxAddressImport
Documentation:
Allows the import of an Autofill profile if duplicate fields were present
with identical field values.
TODO(crbug.com/395855125): Remove when launched.

Name: kPlatformHEVCDecoderSupport
Documentation: must be enabled

Name: kMobilePromoOnDesktop
Documentation: If this feature is enabled, show mobile promo on desktop.

Name: kAutofillAiVoteForFormatStringsForFlightNumbers
Documentation:
If enabled, votes for the format of flight number fields are uploaded. For
example, if there is a flight number "LH89" on file, a submitted value of
"89" on a field with type `FLIGHT_RESERVATION_FLIGHT_NUMBER` uploads "N".

Name: kResumeNavigationWithSpeculativeRFHProcessGone
Documentation:
When enabled, allows a navigation to resume even if the renderer process for
its speculative RFH is killed. This only works for navigations that have not
yet received the response and picked the final RFH to commit in.

Name: kXsurfaceMetricsReporting
Documentation:
Feature that enables xsurface to provide the metrics reporting state to an
xsurface feed.

Name: kNoForcedFrameUpdatesForWebTests
Documentation: Disables forced frame updates for web tests. Used by web test runner only.

Name: kEmbeddingRequiresOptIn
Documentation:
Requires documents embedded via <iframe>, etc, to explicitly opt-into the
embedding: https://github.com/mikewest/embedding-requires-opt-in.

Name: kGPUBlockListTestGroup
Documentation:
This feature allows enabling specific entries in
software_rendering_list.json, via experimentation. The entries must have
test_group property and test_group feature parameter should be set in the
experiment for the entries that need to be enabled.

Name: kLCPPPrefetchSubresource
Documentation:
If enabled, LCPP prefetches the subresources based on LCP prewarmed HTTP disk
cache data.

Name: kUseAudioLatencyFromHAL
Documentation:
Use the (hacky) AudioManager.getOutputLatency() call to get the estimated
hardware latency for a stream for OpenSLES playback.  This is normally not
needed, except for some Android TV devices.

Name: kOrganicRepeatableQueries
Documentation: Organic Repeatable Queries

Name: kForceAllowStorageAccess
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/415223384):
`document.requestStorageAccess` is racy when permission has been overridden
(e.g. via `test_driver.set_permission`). This is because the RFHI in the
browser process may not be aware that the renderer has requested (and gotten)
permission by the time StorageAccessHandle tries to bind mojo endpoints.
This is used in the virtual test suite `force-allow-storage-access` to ensure
no WPTs go stale while we wait on the less temporary fix in the task
linked above.

Name: kWebFeedSort
Documentation: Feature that enables sorting by different heuristics in the web feed.

Name: kPlusAddressPreallocation
Documentation:
When enabled, plus addresses are preallocated to avoid having to query the
server for every reserve call.

Name: kWebRtcAllowWgcScreenZeroHz
Documentation:
When enabled we will tell WebRTC that we want to use the 0Hz mode of the
Windows.Graphics.Capture API based {Screen/Window} capturer, if the WGC
capturer is available and enabled. In this mode, only frames with new content
will be sent to the client leading to to 0fps for a static {Screen/Window}
source.
This flag only has an effect if kWebRtcAllowWgcScreenCapturer is enabled.

Name: kAutofillVirtualViewStructureAndroidPasskeyLongPress
Documentation:
If enabled, at least one passkey must be present to forward passkey requests
to the Android Credential Manager. Users can then always (re-)trigger the
passkey request with a long-press action on webauthn-annotated fields.

Name: kThrottlePasswordChangeDialog
Documentation: Adds throttling logic to password change dialog.

Name: kPrecompileInlineScripts
Documentation:
If enabled, inline scripts will be stream compiled using a background HTML
scanner.

Name: kSendTabToSelfEnableNotificationTimeOut
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, the notification shown to users will disapear
after a fixed timeout. When disabled, instead it will remain until the
user interacts with it either by dismissing or openning it.

Name: kPostPowerMonitorBroadcastReceiverInitToBackground
Documentation:
If enabled, post registering PowerMonitor broadcast receiver to a background
thread,

Name: kDefaultBrowserMagicStackIos
Documentation:
Feature flag to enable the ephemeral Default Browser card in the Magic Stack
on iOS.

Name: kDeviceAuthenticatorAndroidx
Documentation:
The feature is a no-op, it replaces android.hardware.biometrics library on
Android with androidx.biometric.

Name: kFeatureParamWithCache
Documentation:
Controls caching within BASE_FEATURE_PARAM(). This is feature-controlled
so that ScopedFeatureList can disable it to turn off caching.

Name: kPlusAddressUserCreatedMultiplePlusAddressesSurvey
Documentation: TODO: crbug.com/348139343 - Move back to components/plus_addresses.

Name: kEnableVariableRefreshRate
Documentation: Enables the variable refresh rate feature for Borealis gaming only.

Name: kLoadingPreconnectToRedirectTarget
Documentation:
Modifies loading predictor so that the predictions also contain origins of
the redirect target of the navigation.

Name: kDownloadNotificationServiceUnifiedAPI
Documentation:
Whether download notification service uses new unified API based on offline
item and native persistence of notification IDs.

Name: kSafeBrowsingSyncCheckerCheckAllowlist
Documentation:
Enables sync checker to check allowlist first on Chrome on Android. This is
an optimization to improve the speed of Safe Browsing checks.
See go/skip-sync-hpd-allowlist-android for details.

Name: kV8IgnitionElideRedundantTdzChecks
Documentation:
Elide redundant TDZ hole checks in bytecode. This only sets the V8 flag when
manually overridden.

Name: kFreezingWithoutBatterySaver
Documentation: activates freezing of tabs with high background cpu usage

Name: kAutofillCapturedSiteTestsUseAutofillFlow
Documentation:
If enabled, Captured Site Tests will use 'AutofillFlow' utility to trigger
the autofill action. This feature is for testing purposes and is not supposed
to be launched.

Name: kAndroidCaretBrowsing
Documentation:
Enables the caret browsing a11y feature - can use arrow keys to navigate
through web pages.

Name: kSelfSignedLocalNetworkInterstitial
Documentation:
Enables a special interstitial for self signed cert errors in local network
URLs.

Name: kDiscardableMemoryBackingTrial
Documentation: Feature flag enabling the discardable memory backing trial.

Name: kCompressionDictionaryTransportRequireKnownRootCert
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, Chromium will use stored shared dictionaries
only if the request URL is a localhost URL or the transport layer is using a
certificate rooted at a standard CA root.

Name: kSkipFinishDuringReleaseLayerTreeFrameSink
Documentation: A kill switch in case skipping finish causes unexpected issues.

Name: kRestrictAbusePorts
Documentation: Finch-controlled list of ports that should be blocked due to ongoing abuse.

Name: kAdAuctionSignals
Documentation:
Controls the capturing of the Ad-Auction-Signals header, and the maximum
allowed Ad-Auction-Signals header value.

Name: kSlimDirectReceiverIpc
Documentation:
When enabled, slim will receive CompositorFrameSink messages directly without
the intermediate IO-thread hop.

Name: kMitigateLegacySearchEnginePromoOverlap
Documentation:
Mitigate overlap cases between the legacy search engine promo and the
device-based program eligibility determinations.

Name: kLinkCopiedToast
Documentation: Individual toasts

Name: kSharedStorageAPI
Documentation:
Enable the shared storage API. Note that enabling this feature does not
automatically expose this API to the web, it only allows the element to be
enabled by the runtime enabled feature, for origin trials.
https://github.com/pythagoraskitty/shared-storage/blob/main/README.md

Name: kNetworkServiceTaskScheduler
Documentation:
When enabled, Network Service Task Scheduler is enabled on the Network
Service's IO Thread.

Name: kAutofillStructuredFieldsDisableAddressLines
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, the AddressFieldParser does NOT try to parse
address lines once it has found a street name and house number or other
combinations of fields that indicate that an address form uses structured
addresses. This should be the default in all countries with fully supported
structured addresses. However, if a country is not sufficiently modeled,
autofill may still do the right thing if it recognizes "Street name, house
number, address line 2" as a sequence.
TODO(crbug.com/40266693) Remove once launched.

Name: kPrivateAggregationApi
Documentation: Enables the Private Aggregation API.

Name: kSearchEnginePreconnect2
Documentation: Enables a more efficient SearchEnginePreconnector

Name: kSubframePriorityContribution
Documentation:
When enabled, RenderWidgetHost in BFCache doesn't contribute to the priority
of the renderer process.

Name: kGlicActOnWebCapabilityForManagedTrials
Documentation:
Controls whether the Glic's act-on-web capability is checked for managed
trial clients.

Name: kAutofillEnableNewFopDisplayDesktop
Documentation: When enabled, card and IBAN autofill will be shown in new FOP style.

Name: kCloseOmniboxPopupOnInactiveAreaClick
Documentation:
When enabled, clicks outside the omnibox and its popup will close an open
omnibox popup.

Name: kFencedFrames
Documentation:
Enable the <fencedframe> element; see crbug.com/1123606. Note that enabling
this feature does not automatically expose this element to the web, it only
allows the element to be enabled by the runtime enabled feature, for origin
trials.

Name: kWebAssemblyTiering
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly tiering (Liftoff -> TurboFan).

Name: kWebBluetoothAllowGetAvailabilityWithBfcache
Documentation:
When enabled, calling navigator.bluetooth.getAvailability() does not prevent
the frame from entering the back forward cache.

Name: kEnableLazyLoadImageForInvisiblePage
Documentation:
Whether to respect loading=lazy attribute for images when they are on
invisible pages.

Name: kRefreshExpirationDate
Documentation: Whether download expiration date will be refreshed on resumption.

Name: kHintsBatchUpdateForActiveTabsAndTopHosts
Documentation:
Whether batch updates are enabled for active tabs and top hosts.
TODO: crbug.com/421924837 - This only exists to allow tests to exercise this
behavior on platforms where it is disabled. Fix tests and remove this.

Name: kResamplingScrollEventsExperimentalPrediction
Documentation:
Enables resampling of scroll events using an experimental latency of +3.3ms
instead of the original -5ms.

Name: kOnDeviceModelTestFeature
Documentation: Allow on-device model support for Test feature, to be used in tests.

Name: kFeedContainment
Documentation: Feature that enables feed containment.

Name: kNonMilestoneUpdateToast
Documentation: Controls whether to show a toast for Chrome non milestone update.

Name: kHeavyAdInterventionWarning
Documentation:
Enables or disables reporting on the intervention that unloads ad iframes
with intensive resource usage.

Name: kAutofillEnableCvcStorageAndFillingEnhancement
Documentation:
When enabled, will enhance CVV storage project. Provide better suggestion,
resolve conflict with COF project and add logging.

Name: kVaapiVideoMinResolutionForPerformance
Documentation:
Ensure the advertised minimum supported resolution is larger than or equal to
a given one (likely QVGA + 1) for certain codecs/modes and platforms, for
performance reasons. This does not affect JPEG decoding.

NOTE: This feature is default-enabled, but selectively disabled by tests
so they can test resolutions below the threshold.  See crbug.com/40650027

Name: kWorkerThreadSequentialShutdown
Documentation:
WorkerThread termination procedure (prepare and shutdown) runs sequentially
in the same task without calling another cross thread post task.
Kill switch for crbug.com/409059706.

Name: kWebUsb
Documentation:
Controls whether the WebUSB API is enabled:
https://wicg.github.io/webusb

Name: kSafetyHubUnifiedPasswordsModule
Documentation: Enables the unified passwords module in Safety Hub.

Name: kEnableInteractiveOnlyADPFRenderer
Documentation:
If enabled, Chrome's ADPF(Android Dynamic Performance Framework) hint
session includes Renderer threads only if:
- The Renderer is handling an interacton
- The Renderer is the main frame's Renderer, and there no Renderers handling
  an interaction.

Name: kTileOOMFreezeMitigation
Documentation:
When enabled, TileManager running into OOM will forcibly mark tiles as OOM so
that it doesn't wait for resource releases that will never come.

Name: kEnablePortBoundCookies
Documentation: Enables binding of cookies to the port that originally set them by default.

Name: kAccessibilityExposeSummaryAsHeading
Documentation:
Expose <summary>" as a heading instead of a button.
Two reasons to try this:
1. Unlike for a button, JAWS will not enforce leafiness for a heading, so
that things like child links will still be presented to the user.
2. The user can use heading navigation for summaries.
We may decide to scale this back for use cases such as a summary inside of
a table or a list.
Experiment until we validate the approach with ATs and ARIA WG.

Name: kSendCnameAliasesToSubresourceFilterFromBrowser
Documentation:
Enables or disables performing SubresourceFilter checks from the Browser
against any aliases for the requested URL found from DNS CNAME records.

Name: kOptimizationGuideUseContinueOnShutdownForPageContentAnnotations
Documentation:
Enables use of task runner with trait CONTINUE_ON_SHUTDOWN for page content
annotations on-device models.

Name: kRealboxMatchSearchboxTheme
Documentation:
If enabled, the NTP "realbox" will have same border/drop shadow in hover
state as searchbox.

Name: kWebAuthnImmediateGetAutoselect
Documentation: Enables autoselecting the single mechanism in immediate mediation requests.

Name: kSyncMoveValuablesToProfileDb
Documentation: Enables storing valuables in the profile db instead of the account db.

Name: kAllowClientCertificateReportingForUsers
Documentation: Allows the reporting of client certificates for managed users.

Name: kUnloadBlocklisted
Documentation:
If enabled, the usage of unload handlers causes a blocklisted reason for
BFCache. The purpose is to capture their source location.

Name: kGPayAppDynamicUpdate
Documentation:
If enabled, the GooglePayPaymentApp handles communications between the native
GPay app and the browser for dynamic updates on shipping and payment data.

Name: kMediaDrmPreprovisioningAtStartup
Documentation:
Determines if MediaDrmOriginIdManager should attempt to pre-provision origin
IDs at startup (whenever a profile is loaded). Also used by tests that
disable it so that the tests can setup before pre-provisioning is done.
Note: Has no effect if kMediaDrmPreprovisioning feature is disabled.

Name: kServiceWorkerBackgroundUpdateForRegisteredStorageKeys
Documentation:
If enabled, UI thread tasks can check ServiceWorker registration information
from the thread pool without waiting for running the receiving task. Please
see crbug.com/421530699 for more details.

Name: kSafetyHubAndroidSurvey
Documentation: Enables Safety Hub HaTS survey on Android.

Name: kNtpDriveModuleShowSixFiles
Documentation: If enabled, six files show in the NTP Drive module, instead of three.

Name: kHttpsFirstBalancedMode
Documentation:
Enables HTTPS-First Mode in a balanced configuration that doesn't warn on
HTTP when HTTPS can't be reasonably expected.

Name: kAudioFocusSessionGrouping
Documentation:
Enables Audio Focus grouping which means that multiple media sessions can
share audio focus at the same time provided that they have the same group id.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformDeviceSwitcher
Documentation: Feature flag for device switcher segment.

Name: kGlicActorIterativeInteractionPointDiscovery
Documentation:
Controls whether the actor framework searches for an interaction point when
when the center of the target element is obscured.

Name: kAutofillUseNegativePatternForAllAttributes
Documentation:
When enabled, the form field parser won't try to match other attributes if
any of the negative patterns matched.

Name: kWebAppSystemMediaControls
Documentation: Enables per PWA System Media Controls. Only supported on Windows and macOS.

Name: kLoadingPredictorPrefetchUseReadAndDiscardBody
Documentation:
Use the kURLLoadOptionReadAndDiscardBody option to URLLoader to avoid
unnecessarily copying response body data.

Name: kThrottleUnimportantFrameTimers
Documentation:
Throttles Javascript timer wake ups of unimportant frames (cross origin
frames with small proportion of the page's visible area and no user
activation) on foreground pages.

Name: kRestrictCloneParameters
Documentation:
When enabled, restrict clone to just flags used by fork and pthread_create on
android.

Name: kScrollJankV4Metric
Documentation: When enabled, the V4 scroll jank metric will be emitted.

Name: kKeepAliveInBrowserMigration
Documentation:
Kill-switch for the fetch keepalive request infra migration.
If enabled, all keepalive requests will be proxied via the browser process.
Design Doc: https://bit.ly/chromium-keepalive-migration
Tracker: https://crbug.com/1356128

Name: kAutofillDisableFilling
Documentation: Kill switch for Autofill filling.

Name: kFedCmIdPRegistration
Documentation: Enables usage of the FedCM IdP Registration API.

Name: kV8VmFuture
Documentation: Enables future V8 VM features

Name: kInterestFeedV2
Documentation:
InterestFeedV2 takes precedence over InterestFeedContentSuggestions.
InterestFeedV2 is cached in ChromeCachedFlags. If the default value here is
changed, please update the cached one's default value in CachedFeatureFlags.

Name: kPushMessagingDisallowSenderIDs
Documentation: Feature flag to disallow creation of push messages with GCM Sender IDs.

Name: kDestroyProfileOnBrowserClose
Documentation:
Destroy profiles when their last browser window is closed, instead of when
the browser exits.

Name: kDevToolsAiGeneratedTimelineLabels
Documentation: Whether the DevTools AI generated annotation labels in timeline are enabled.

Name: kIsolatesPriorityBestEffortWhenHidden
Documentation:
When enabled, forces the priority of isolates in hidden renderers to
best-effort, overriding the effect of kIsolatesPriorityUseProcessPriority
(isolates in visible renderer will still get their priority derived from
process priority).

Name: kAndroidMediaPickerAdoption
Documentation: Controls how the Android Media Picker will be introduced.

Name: kOnDeviceModelFetchPerformanceClassEveryStartup
Documentation:
Whether performance class should be fetched each startup or just after a
version update.

Name: kPrivateMetricsWebUI
Documentation: Enables a "Private Metrics" tab in the chrome://metrics-internals page.

Name: kLensOverlayStraightToSrp
Documentation: Enables straight to SRP flows are enabled in the Lens overlay.

Name: kUseLockFreeBloomFilter
Documentation: If enabled, LockFreeAddressHashSet will use the bloom filter.

Name: kForceStartupSigninPromo
Documentation: Features to trigger the startup sign-in promo at boot.

Name: kExtensionLocalizationGuid
Documentation:
Allow e.g. .css files to use default_locale messages in WAR files via GUID.
TODO(crbug.com/435609878): Remove after m142. It's for safe m141 back merge.

Name: kGroupingFrameworkForNonZPS
Documentation:
Features that affect the "twiddle" step of AutocompleteController, e.g.,
deduping or `SortAndCull()`.

Name: kCheckDocumentSequenceNumber
Documentation: TODO(https://crbug.com/40229455): Remove this once established to be safe.

Name: kUseCertTransparencyAwareApiForOsCertVerify
Documentation:
If enabled, Android OS's certificate verification (CertVerifyProcAndroid) is
done using the certificate transparency aware API.

Name: kSwipeToMoveCursor
Documentation: Android only feature, for swipe to move cursor.

Name: kDeviceBoundSessionSigningQuotaAndCaching
Documentation:
This feature controls whether DBSC has a signing quota instead of a refresh
quota, and has associated signing caching for refreshes.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformSignalDbCache
Documentation: Feature flag for turning of signal database cache.

Name: kAndroidUseCorrectWindowBounds
Documentation:
Use Android WindowManager's WindowMetrics as the data source for top-level
browser window bounds in Blink.

Name: kUseCECFlagInPolicyData
Documentation: Controls if we can use the cec flag in PolicyData.

Name: kAddTaskLeewayFeature
Documentation:
Under this feature, a non-zero leeway is added to delayed tasks. Along with
DelayPolicy, this affects the time at which a delayed task runs.

Name: kFencedFramesLocalUnpartitionedDataAccess
Documentation:
Controls functionality related to network revocation/local unpartitioned
data access in fenced frames.

Name: kSyncReadingListBatchUploadSelectedItems
Documentation:
If enabled, support displaying and uploading individual Reading List items in
the Batch Upload UI.

Batch Upload of all items is supported regardless of this feature flag.

On Windows/Mac/Linux: this flag only affects behavior if the
`syncer::kReadingListEnableSyncTransportModeUponSignIn` feature is also
enabled.

On Android: this flag does not affect user-visiable behavior, but does enable
new code paths.

Name: kNavigationThrottleRegistryAttributeCache
Documentation:
When enabled, NavigationThrottleRegistry will cache attribute query results
for the next same query. See https://crbug.com/424460302.

Name: kSiteIsolationForPasswordSites
Documentation:
Controls a mode for dynamically process-isolating sites where the user has
entered a password.  This is intended to be used primarily when full site
isolation is turned off.  To check whether this mode is enabled, use
SiteIsolationPolicy::IsIsolationForPasswordSitesEnabled() rather than
checking the feature directly, since that decision is influenced by other
factors as well.

Name: kOpsDisplayScaleFactor
Documentation:
Open Pluggable Specification (OPS) is a special industry standard with
slot-in computing modules.

Name: kEnableCompose
Documentation: Controls whether the Compose feature is available

Name: kLensOverlayVisualSelectionUpdates
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay visual selection updates.

Name: kEnterpriseBadgingForNtpFooterWithOverThreePolicies
Documentation:
Enables enterprise badging for managed browsers with local management only
AND 3 or more policies on the new tab page footer.

Name: kAutofillAcceptDomMutationAfterAutofillSubmission
Documentation:
If enabled, we start forwarding submissions with source
DOM_MUTATION_AFTER_AUTOFILL, even for non-password forms.

Name: kPlusAddressDeclinedFirstTimeCreateSurvey
Documentation: TODO: crbug.com/348139343 - Move back to components/plus_addresses.

Name: kStopInBackground
Documentation:
Freeze scheduler task queues in background after allowed grace time.
"stop" is a legacy name.

Name: kContextualPageActionTabGrouping
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling tab grouping action feature.

Name: kCustomizeChromeWallpaperSearch
Documentation:
If enabled, shows wallpaper search within the Customize Chrome Side Panel.
This is a kill switch. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kUserBypassFeedback
Documentation: Feature to enable the feedback button in the User Bypass UI.

Name: kSuppressIntermediateACUpdatesOnLowEndDevices
Documentation:
Prevents intermediate AutocompleteResult updates from being sent to Java on
low-end devices. This aims at eliminating time spent on constructing,
measuring, and laying out views that are about to be discarded, and reducing
the volume of JNI jumps.

Name: kUpdateStateBeforeUnbinding
Documentation: Update child process binding state before unbinding.

Name: kPersistFailedLaunchState
Documentation:
If enabled, then failed launch state persisted to prefs. Disabling this
feature can be used to 'reset' clients back to a state where they are once
again attempting to launch sandboxed network services e.g. if a bug fix lands
and it is not desirable to wait until the next milestone. Note that even if
this feature is disabled any failed launches in the current browser session
will still result in sandbox being disabled for the lifetime of the running
browser.

Name: kFledgeAlwaysReuseBidderContext
Documentation: Reuse a single V8 context to generate all bids in a bidder worklet.

Name: kDelayAsyncScriptExecution
Documentation:
If enabled, async script execution will be delayed than usual.
See https://crbug.com/1340837.

As of 2023/11, this experiment enables kLCPCriticalPathPredictor.
See third_party/blink/common/loader/lcp_critical_path_predictor_util.cc

Name: kSplitCacheByCrossSiteMainFrameNavigationBoolean
Documentation:
This flag incorporates a boolean into the cache key that is true for
renderer-initiated main frame navigations when the request initiator site is
cross-site to the URL being navigated to. This provides protections against
certain cross-site leak attacks involving cross-site navigations.

Name: kAggressiveShaderCacheLimits
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kDedicatedMediaServiceThread
Documentation: Runs the media service in the GPU process on a dedicated thread.

Name: kVisitedURLRankingDeduplication
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling URL visit resumption deduplication.

Name: kAutofillAiFillingSurvey
Documentation:
When enabled, a HaTS survey is shown after a walletable suggestion is
displayed and the form submitted. The survey does not require the suggestion
to be accepted.

Name: kJavaScriptImportAttributes
Documentation: Enables the `with` syntax for the Import Attributes proposal.

Name: kDisableSyncAutogeneratedSearchEngines
Documentation:
Switch guarding TemplateURL syncing of untouched autogenerated search
engines.

Name: kConsumeCodeCacheOffThread
Documentation: Controls off-thread code cache consumption.

Name: kCustomizeChromeWallpaperSearchButton
Documentation:
If enabled, shows entry point on Customize Chrome Side Panel's Appearance
page for Wallpaper Search.";

Name: kMediaOptimizer
Documentation:
Enable the prototype global optimization of tuneables via finch.  See
media/base/tuneable.h for how to create tuneable parameters.

Name: kMessagesAndroidExtraHistograms
Documentation: Feature that enables extra histogram recordings.

Name: kEnablePixPaymentsInLandscapeMode
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome will offer to pay with accounts supporting Pix to users
using their devices in landscape mode. Chrome always offers to pay with Pix
accounts for users using their devices in portrait mode.

Name: kSplitCacheByIncludeCredentials
Documentation: Splits cache entries by the request's includeCredentials.

Name: kDisablePrivacySandboxPrompts
Documentation:
Disables any Privacy Sandbox related prompts. Should only be used for testing
purposes. This feature is used to support external automated testing using
Chrome, where additional prompts break behavior expectations.

Name: kBlockMidiByDefault
Documentation: Block all MIDI access with the MIDI_SYSEX permission

Name: kAutofillSkipSaveCardForTabModalPopup
Documentation:
Kill switch, when enabled, will prevent the display of the save card bubble
within a tab modal pop-up window.

Name: kSecurePaymentConfirmation
Documentation:
Browser-side feature flag for Secure Payment Confirmation (SPC) that also
controls the render side feature state. SPC is not currently available on
Linux or ChromeOS, as it requires platform authenticator support.

Name: kLogUrlScoringSignals
Documentation: Omnibox ML scoring.

Name: kLocalNetworkAccessForWorkers
Documentation:
Enables Local Network Access checks for all types of web workers.

The exact checks run are the same as for other document subresources, and
depends on the state of the main Local Network Access feature flags
`kLocalNetworkAccessChecks`.

Name: kCookieIndicesHeader
Documentation:
If enabled, then the network service will parse the Cookie-Indices header.
This does not currently control changing cache behavior according to the
value of this header.

Name: kWebUIBundledCodeCache
Documentation:
Enables build-time generated resource-bundled code caches for WebUI pages.
See crbug.com/375509504 for details.

Name: kSharedStorageTransactionalBatchUpdate
Documentation:
Enables transactional behavior for sharedStorage.batchUpdate(). This also
disallows the 'withLock' option for methods within batchUpdate().
https://wicg.github.io/shared-storage/#batch-update

Name: kAutofillPaymentsFieldSwapping
Documentation:
When enabled, focusing on a credit card number field that was traditionally
autofilled will yield all credit card suggestions.
TODO(crbug.com/354175563): Remove when launched.

Name: kEnableBestEffortTaskInhibitingPolicy
Documentation: Enable best effort task inhibiting based on performance scenario information.

Name: kLensOverlayContextualSearchbox
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay searchbox.

Name: kHttpsFirstBalancedModeAutoEnable
Documentation:
Automatically enables HTTPS-First Mode in a balanced configuration when
possible.

Name: kCombineNewWindowIPCs
Documentation:
When enabled, CreateNewWindow() and ShowCreatedWindow() mojo calls are
coalesced into a single call to CreateNewWindow().

Name: kSegmentationPlatformPowerUserFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling Power user segmentation.

Name: kDestroySystemProfiles
Documentation:
DestroyProfileOnBrowserClose only covers deleting regular (non-System)
Profiles. This flags lets us destroy the System Profile, as well.

Name: kAutofillAndroidDesktopSuppressAccessoryOnEmpty
Documentation:
If enabled, on Android desktop, Autofill keyboard accessory will be
suppressed when there are no autofill suggestions.

Name: kTimeoutTcpConnectAttempt
Documentation:
Enables a timeout on individual TCP connect attempts, based on
the parameter values.

Name: kDynamicMaxAutocomplete
Documentation:
Feature used to cap max suggestions to a dynamic limit based on how many URLs
would be shown. E.g., show up to 10 suggestions if doing so would display no
URLs; else show up to 8 suggestions if doing so would include 1 or more URLs.

Name: kPlusAddressOfferCreationOnAllNonUsernameFields
Documentation:
When enabled, plus address creation is offered on all email fields that are
not a username field - even if they are on a login form or a change password
form.
Intended as a killswitch to protect against unexpected behavior.
TODO: crbug.com/355398505 - clean up.

Name: kBlockCrossPartitionBlobUrlFetching
Documentation:
Please keep features in alphabetical order.
Enables blob URL fetches to fail when cross-partition.

Name: kWebBluetoothNewPermissionsBackend
Documentation:
Controls whether Web Bluetooth should use the new permissions backend. The
new permissions backend uses ObjectPermissionContextBase, which is used by
other device APIs, such as WebUSB. When enabled,
WebBluetoothWatchAdvertisements and WebBluetoothGetDevices blink features are
also enabled.

Name: kAAudioPerStreamDeviceSelection
Documentation:
Enables selection of audio devices for each individual AAudio stream instead
of using communication streams and managing the system-wide communication
route. This is not fully reliable on all Android devices.

Requires `UseAAudioDriver` and `UseAAudioInput`, otherwise it will have no
effect.

Name: kCastVideoEncoderFrameDrop
Documentation: A video encoder is allowed to drop a frame in cast mirroring.

Name: kAutofillEnableFillingPhoneCountryCodesByAddressCountryCodes
Documentation:
Improves the selection of phone country codes by also considering address
country codes / names.
See GetStreetAddressForInput() in field_filling_address_util.cc for a details
description.
TODO(crbug.com/40249216). Clean up when launched.

Name: kPushMessagingGcmEndpointWebpushPath
Documentation: Feature flag to control use of new /wp/ path based Webpush endpoints.

Name: kEnablePreferencesAccountStorage
Documentation: Enables a separate account-scoped storage for preferences.

Name: kLocalNetworkAccessForNavigationsWarningOnly
Documentation:
Enables Local Network Access checks in warning mode for main frame
navigations.

Does nothing if `kLocalNetworkAccessForNavigations` is disabled.

If both this and `kLocalNetworkAccessChecksForNavigations` are enabled, then
main frame navigations that qualify as LNA requests do not require a
permission, but simply display a warning in DevTools.

Name: kDefaultTypedNavigationsToHttps
Documentation: Navigation experiments.

Name: kEnhancedSafeBrowsingPromo
Documentation: Enables Enhanced Safe Browsing promos for iOS.

Name: kDsePreload2OnPress
Documentation: Enables on-press prefetch.

Name: kDeleteExpiredDownloads
Documentation: Whether to delete expired download.

Name: kAutofillEnableFpanRiskBasedAuthentication
Documentation:
When enabled, server card retrieval will begin with a risk-based check
instead of jumping straight to CVC or biometric auth.

Name: kAutofillAiIdentityAndTravelPrefs
Documentation:
Kill switch: If enabled, MayPerformAutofillAiAction() also depends on two
prefs that enable/disable filling and import of identity-related and
travel-related entities.
TODO(crbug.com/450060416): Remove after M144 branch point (2025-01-12).

Name: kSearchEngineChoiceTriggerReprompt
Documentation:
Reprompt params for the search engine choice.
This is a JSON dictionary where keys are country codes, and values are Chrome
version strings. The wildcard country '*' represents all countries.
When a specific country is specified, it takes precedence over the wildcard.

Example: {"*": "2.0.0.0", "BE": "5.0.0.0"}
This reprompts users in Belgium who made the choice strictly before version
5, and users in all other countries who made the choice strictly before
version 2.

Name: kConfirmSuggestionRemovals
Documentation:
The features should be documented alongside the definition of their values in
the .cc file.

Name: kUseAAudioDriver
Documentation:
Enables loading and using AAudio instead of OpenSLES on compatible devices,
for audio output streams. This feature is disabled on ATV HDMI dongle devices
as OpenSLES provides more accurate output latency on those devices.

TODO(crbug.com/401365323): Remove this feature in the future.

Name: kUserLevelMemoryPressureSignalMetricsOnly
Documentation:
An experiment to collect memory metrics on all devices to determine the most
suitable memory heuristics. Memory pressure signals will not be sent in the
experiment group.

Name: kPaintPreviewDemo
Documentation:
Used to enable a main menu item on Android that captures and displays a paint
preview for the current page. The paint preview UI will be dismissed on back
press and all associated stored files deleted. This intended to test whether
capturing and playing paint preview works on a specific site.

Name: kGCMDoNotIncreaseBackoffDelayOnNetworkChange
Documentation:
When enabled, the first connection attempt won't contribute to backoff
exponential delay. This will mitigate issues when there is no network
connection yet but a lot of network changes.

Name: kClientHintsDPR_DEPRECATED
Documentation: Enable legacy `dpr` client hint.

Name: kComposeAutoSubmit
Documentation: Enables Auto-submit of compose with a valid selection.

Name: kAutofillAiWalletVehicleRegistration
Documentation:
If enabled, AutofillAi supports vehicle registration entities from Google
Wallet.

Name: kOmniboxHistoryClusterProvider
Documentation:
Enables the `HistoryClusterProvider` to surface Journeys as a suggestion row
instead of an action chip. Enabling this won't actually disable
`kOmniboxAction` but for user experiments, the intent is to only have 1
enabled. `kJourneys` must also be enabled for this to take effect.

Name: kTriggerPasswordResyncWhenUndecryptablePasswordsDetected
Documentation: Starts passwords resync when undecryptable passwords are detected.

Name: kFledgeEnforcePermissionPolicyContributeOnEvent
Documentation:
Enable enforcement of permission policy for
privateAggregation.contributeToHistogramOnEvent.

Name: kMetricsReportingFeature
Documentation:
Metrics reporting feature. This feature, along with user consent, controls if
recording and reporting are enabled. If the feature is enabled, but no
consent is given, then there will be no recording or reporting.

Name: kReaderModeDistillInApp
Documentation: Feature declarations below -- alphabetical order.

Name: kSynchronousPageFlipTesting
Documentation:
Indicates whether DrmOverlayManager should used the synchronous API to
perform pageflip tests.

Name: kNavigationConfidenceEpsilon
Documentation:
Controls the configurablity of the navigation confidence noise level.
If the feature is not enabled, then the epsilon value will be 1.1.

Name: kFeedNoViewCache
Documentation: When enabled, no view cache is used.

Name: kLensOverlayForceEmptyCsbQuery
Documentation:
Force Lens overlay invocations to perform an empty CSB query. For internal
debugging only.

Name: kSpdySessionForProxyAdditionalChecks
Documentation:
Enables more checks when creating a SpdySession for proxy. These checks are
already applied to non-proxy SpdySession creations.
TODO(crbug.com/343519247): Remove this once we are sure that these checks are
not causing any problems.

Name: kReturnDeniedForNotificationsWhenNoAppLevelSettings
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome returns "DENIED" (instead of "ASK") as permission state
for notifications if Chrome does not have and cannot acquire app-level
permissions on Android.

Name: kAutofillEnableSaveAndFill
Documentation:
When enabled, the 'Save and Fill' suggestion will be offered in the credit
card dropdown menu for users who don't have any cards saved in Autofill.

Name: kAutofillUnionTypesSingleTypeInAutofillInformation
Documentation:
If enabled, ensures that the "autofill-information" attribute only contains a
single FieldType in "overall type: <FieldTypes>". For example,
"overall type: NAME_FULL, USERNAME" becomes "overall type: NAME_FULL" if the
feature is enabled.
TODO(crbug.com/435354393): Migrate the infrastructure to union types and
remove this feature.

Name: kLocalCompileHints
Documentation:
Cache information about which functions are compiled and use it for eager-
compiling those functions when the same script is loaded again.

Name: kMediaStreamTrackTransfer
Documentation: Allow cross-context transfer of MediaStreamTracks.

Name: kUseSecurityLevelWhenCheckingMediaDrmVersion
Documentation:
Specify the required security level for MediaDrm when checking the MediaDrm
version.

Name: kBrowsingTopicsParameters
Documentation:
Decoupled with the main `kBrowsingTopics` feature, so it allows us to
decouple the server side configs.

Name: kPrivateAggregationDebugReportingCookieDeprecationTesting
Documentation:
Enables Private Aggregation debug reporting to be enabled during the
third-party cookie deprecation experiment.

Name: kFileSystemAccessMoveWithOverwrite
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kAllowMediaCodecSoftwareDecoder
Documentation:
Allow the media pipeline to prioritize the software decoder provided by
MediaCodec, instead of the built-in software decoders. This is only enabled
for platforms which shows worse performance when using the built-in software
decoders, e.g. Cast on ATV.

Name: kEnableGenericOidcAuthProfileManagement
Documentation: Controls whether the generic OIDC-response profile management is enabled.

Name: kAutofillAcrossIframesIos
Documentation: All features in alphabetical order.

Name: kClientSideDetectionShowLlamaScamVerdictWarning
Documentation:
Show a warning to the user based on the
IntelligentScanVerdict::SCAM_EXPERIMENT_VERDICT_2.

Name: kUseButtonTranslateBubbleUi
Documentation: This feature uses the existing UI for the Full Page Translate bubble.

Name: kSecurePaymentConfirmationUseCredentialStoreAPIs
Documentation:
Used to control whether SecurePaymentConfirmation is able to rely on OS-level
credential store APIs, or if it can only rely on the user-profile database.

Name: kClearSiteDataPrefetchPrerenderCache
Documentation:
If enabled, the Clear-Site-Data header will handle "prefetchCache" and
"prerenderCache" to clear the Prefetch and Prerender caches respectively.

Name: kWebRTCColorAccuracy
Documentation:
Inform webrtc with correct video color space information whenever
possible.

Name: kWebAuthnNewRefreshFlow
Documentation:
Controls setting the `create_new_vault` flag when refreshing a PIN. When
enabled, the enclave will produce new Vault parameters to create a new Vault
instead of replacing it.

Name: kRedWarningSurvey
Documentation: Enables HaTS surveys for users encountering red warnings.

Name: kBackForwardCacheUnloadAllowed
Documentation:
Controls the interaction between back/forward cache and
unload. When enabled, pages with unload handlers may enter the
cache.

Name: kAutofillAiWithDataSchema
Documentation: Enables the second iteration AutofillAI.

Name: kUseNewAlpsCodepointHttp2
Documentation:
Enables using the new ALPS codepoint to negotiate application settings for
HTTP2.

Name: kMlUrlScoring
Documentation:
If enabled, runs the ML scoring model to assign new relevance scores to the
URL suggestions and reranks them.

Name: kSpdyHeadersToHttpResponseUseBuilder
Documentation: Enables a more efficient implementation of SpdyHeadersToHttpResponse().

Name: kBrowsingTopics
Documentation:
https://github.com/patcg-individual-drafts/topics
Kill switch for the Topics API.

Name: kConnectionKeepAliveForHttp2
Documentation: Enables Connection Keep-Alive feature for Http2

Name: kCastDeviceFilter
Documentation: Used in downstream code.

Name: kPreloadingConfig
Documentation:
This Feature allows configuring preloading features via a parameter string.
See content/browser/preloading/preloading_config.cc to see how to use this
feature.

Name: kPhoneHubStructuredMetrics
Documentation: Controls whether Phone Hub Structured Metrics is enabled or not.

Name: kJourneysImages
Documentation: Enables images for Journeys in UI.

Name: kVariableRefreshRateAvailable
Documentation:
This feature indicates that this device should have variable refresh rates
enabled by default if available. This overrides the default value of
|kEnableVariableRefreshRate|. This flag is added by cros-config and not
exposed in the chrome://flags UI.

Name: kNtpSharepointModule
Documentation: If enabled, sharepoint module will be shown.

Name: kShouldRequestConfigurationFile
kSyncWalletFlightReservations
Documentation: Enables syncing of flight reservations coming from Google Wallet.

Name: kSecPurposePrefetchHeaderNoStatePrefetch
Documentation:
If enabled, prefetches from NoStatePrefetchURLLoaderThrottle will be sent
with the Sec-Purpose: "prefetch" header.

Name: kEnableIpProtectionProxy
Documentation: Enables custom proxy configuration for the IP Protection experimental proxy.

Name: kDeviceBoundSessionProactiveRefresh
Documentation:
This feature controls whether to proactively trigger Device
Bound Session refreshes when a cookie is soon to expire.

Name: kWebAppsEnableMLModelForPromotion
Documentation: ML Installability promotion flags and all the feature params.

Name: kAutofillAiKnownTravelerNumber
Documentation: If enabled, AutofillAi supports known traveler numbers.

Name: kPostFREFixMetricsReportingFeature
Documentation:
Same as |kMetricsReportingFeature|, but this feature is associated with a
different trial, which has different sampling rates. This is due to a bug
in which the old sampling rate was not being applied correctly. In order for
the fix to not affect the overall sampling rate, this new feature was
created. See crbug/1306481.

Name: kTabModalUsesDesktopWidget
Documentation: If enabled, use desktop widget to show tab modal dialogs.

Name: kRecordLastUnsentLogMetadataMetrics
Documentation:
The feature to record the unsent log info metrics, refer to
UnsentLogStoreMetricsImpl::RecordLastUnsentLogMetadataMetrics.

Name: kRemoveWakeLockInDestructor
Documentation:
Enables removing wake locks in the WakeLock destructor if non-null. Serves as
killswitch while we roll out this functionality. TODO(crbug.com/349860794):
Remove this killswitch post-safe rollout.

Name: kLensOverlayPermissionBubbleAlt
Documentation: Use alternate appearance for permission bubble.

Name: kPrefetchCanaryCheckerParams
Documentation: Controls field trials parameters for prefetch canary checker.

Name: kUserLevelMemoryPressureSignalOn3GbDevices
Documentation: (for Android 3GB devices)

Name: kSharedStorageAPIEnableWALForDatabase
Documentation:
Enables WAL (write-ahead-logging) mode for the Shared Storage API SQLite
database backend.

Name: kSmartSuggestionForLargeDownloads
Documentation: Whether to enable smart suggestion for large downloads

Name: kHardwareSecureDecryptionAv1
Documentation:
Enables hardware secure AV1 decoding if supported by the hardware
and the OS Content Decryption Module (CDM).

Name: kAutofillShowBubblesBasedOnPriorities
Documentation:
When enabled, password manager and autofill bubbles will be shown based on
the priorities of the bubbles.
TODO(crbug.com/432429605): Remove when launched.

Name: kEnableComposeSavedStateNotification
Documentation: Controls whether or not the saved state notification is shown.

Name: kPostMessageThirdPartyToFirstPartyDifferentBucketSameOriginBlocked
Documentation:
Whether third-party to first-party different-bucket same-origin post messages
are blocked.

Name: kSafetyHubAndroidSurveyV2
Documentation: Enables new triggers for the Safety Hub HaTS survey on Android.

Name: kFeedAudioOverviews
Documentation: Feature that enables feed audio overviews.

Name: kViewTransitionCaptureAndDisplay
Documentation:
A mode of ViewTransition capture that does not display unstyled frame,
instead displays the properly constructed frame while at the same doing
capture.

Name: kVideoPictureInPictureControlsUpdate2024
Documentation: Displays new video picture-in-picture controls for the 2024 UI update.

Name: kCheckVisibilityInChangePasswordFormWaiter
Documentation:
Checks if the new password field is visible in the viewport before returning
the form in the ChangePasswordFormWaiter.

Name: kAudioFocusDuckFlash
Documentation:
Enables flash to be ducked by audio focus. This is enabled on Chrome OS which
has audio focus enabled.

Name: kNtpModulesOrder
Documentation:
Dummy feature to set param "NtpModulesOrderParam".
This is used for an emergency Finch param. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kWebRtcUseMinMaxVEADimensions
Documentation: Instructs WebRTC to honor the Min/Max Video Encode Accelerator dimensions.

Name: kAudioServiceSandbox
Documentation:
Enables the audio-service sandbox. This feature has an effect only when the
kAudioServiceOutOfProcess feature is enabled.

Name: kExperimentalOmniboxLabs
Documentation:
Controls whether omnibox extensions can use the new capability to intercept
input without needing keyword mode.

Name: kEnableStaticQrCodeForPix
Documentation: When enabled, static qr code will be supported for pix pay flow.

Name: kLaunchWindowsNativeHostsDirectly
Documentation:
Launches Native Host executables directly on Windows rather than using a
cmd.exe process as a proxy.

Name: kFledgeNumberSellerWorkletGroupByOriginContextsToKeep
Documentation:
If kFledgeNumberSellerWorkletGroupByOriginContextsToKeep is enabled,
kFledgeNumberSellerWorkletGroupByOriginContextsToKeepValue sets the number of
previously-used group-by-origin contexts to keep in case they can be reused
in a bidder worklet. Defaulted to 10.

Name: kPrivateMetricsFeature
Documentation:
Enables Private Metrics reporting. This flag enables the flow for reporting
`PrivateMetricReport` protocol buffer as described in
go/chrome-trusted-private-metrics and go/etld-plus-one-metrics.

Name: kPushSubscriptionChangeEventOnInvalidation
Documentation:
Fires the `pushsubscriptionchange` event defined here:
https://w3c.github.io/push-api/#the-pushsubscriptionchange-event
for subscription refreshes, revoked permissions or subscription losses

Name: kOriginIsolationForJsOptExceptions
Documentation:
In order to have broader support for JavaScript optimizer exceptions, we'll
apply origin isolation on navigation for URLs that match rules in the
JAVASCRIPT_OPTIMIZER content setting that don't match the default setting.
TODO(crbug.com/413695645): we want this feature to start isolating any origin
that was specified in the rules but there currently isn't a way to determine
this from the host_content_settings_map API, so we'll improve this in the
future.

On Android, this implicitly starts isolating origins under partial site
isolation. If full site isolation is enabled (examples: through opt-in or an
enterprise policy), then this feature behaves the same as on Desktop.

On Desktop, this feature starts isolating origins where the custom policy
targets an origin that is not already origin-isolated.

Name: kAndroidCaptureKeyEvents
Documentation:
Capture Android key event objects to send them to the web contents when the
IME sends composition texts.

Name: kDsePreload2
Documentation:
DefaultSearchEngine Preload v2

- Base feature flag for DSE preload 2.
- Disables `SearchPrefetch` (DSE v1).
- Enables on-suggest preloads.

https://crbug.com/394988793

Name: kFilteringScrollPrediction
Documentation:
Enables filtering of predicted scroll events on compositor thread.
Uses the kFilterName* values in ui_base_features.h as the 'filter' feature
param.

Name: kLessAggressiveParkableString
Documentation:
Enables more conservative settings for ParkableString: suspend parking in
foreground, and increase aging tick intervals.

Name: kBFCacheOpenBroadcastChannel
Documentation: If enabled, open broadcast channels do not block back/forward cache.

Name: kTextSafetyClassifier
Documentation: Whether to download the text safety classifier model.

Name: kNoThrottlingVisibleAgent
Documentation: Don't throttle frames that are same-agent with with a visible frame.

Name: kAutofillEnableCacheForRegexMatching
Documentation:
